8 season. On 2 May 2018, his contract with Fortaleza was terminated. At the end of the month, he moved abroad and joined Cypriot club APOEL on a season long loan deal.","strDescriptionDE":null,"strDescriptionFR":null,"strDescriptionCN":null,"strDescriptionIT":null,"strDescriptionJP":null,"strDescriptionRU":null,"strDescriptionES":null,"strDescriptionPT":null,"strDescriptionSE":null,"strDescriptionNL":null,"strDescriptionHU":null,"strDescriptionNO":null,"strDescriptionIL":null,"strDescriptionPL":null,"strGender":"Male","strSide":"Right","strPosition":"Left Wing","strCollege":null,"strFacebook":"","strWebsite":"","strTwitter":"","strInstagram":"","strYoutube":"","strHeight":"175 cm","strWeight":"161 lbs","intLoved":"0","strThumb":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/thumb/m3wdhn1716376231.jpg","strPoster":null,"strCutout":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/cutout/s9t6aq1716376257.png","strCartoon":null,"strRender":null,"strBanner":null,"strFanart1":null,"strFanart2":null,"strFanart3":null,"strFanart4":null,"strCreativeCommons":"No","strLocked":"unlocked","strLastName":"Natel"},{"idPlayer":"34233203","idTeam":"141182","idTeam2":null,"idTeamNational":null,"idAPIfootball":"42163","idPlayerManager":null,"idWikidata":null,"idTransferMkt":null,"idESPN":null,"strNationality":"Brazil","strPlayer":"Lucca Borges de Brito","strPlayerAlternate":null,"strTeam":"Novorizontino","strTeam2":null,"strSport":"Soccer","intSoccerXMLTeamID":null,"dateBorn":"1990-02-14","dateDied":null,"strNumber":null,"dateSigned":null,"strSigning":null,"strWage":null,"strOutfitter":null,"strKit":null,"strAgent":null,"strBirthLocation":"Alto Parnaíba, Brazil","strEthnicity":"Hispanic","strStatus":"Active","strDescriptionEN":null,"strDescriptionDE":null,"strDescriptionFR":null,"strDescriptionCN":null,"strDescriptionIT":null,"strDescriptionJP":null,"strDescriptionRU":null,"strDescriptionES":null,"strDescriptionPT":null,"strDescriptionSE":null,"strDescriptionNL":null,"strDescriptionHU":null,"strDescriptionNO":null,"strDescriptionIL":null,"strDescriptionPL":null,"strGender":"Male","strSide":null,"strPosition":"Midfielder","strCollege":null,"strFacebook":null,"strWebsite":null,"strTwitter":null,"strInstagram":null,"strYoutube":null,"strHeight":"178 cm","strWeight":"73 kg","intLoved":"0","strThumb":null,"strPoster":null,"strCutout":null,"strCartoon":null,"strRender":null,"strBanner":null,"strFanart1":null,"strFanart2":null,"strFanart3":null,"strFanart4":null,"strCreativeCommons":"No","strLocked":"unlocked","strLastName":"Brito"},{"idPlayer":"34202472","idTeam":"141182","idTeam2":"0","idTeamNational":null,"idAPIfootball":"10429","idPlayerManager":null,"idWikidata":"Q17318574","idTransferMkt":null,"idESPN":"222443","strNationality":"Brazil","strPlayer":"Marlon","strPlayerAlternate":"","strTeam":"Novorizontino","strTeam2":"","strSport":"Soccer","intSoccerXMLTeamID":null,"dateBorn":"1990-02-26","dateDied":null,"strNumber":"25","dateSigned":null,"strSigning":"","strWage":"","strOutfitter":"","strKit":"","strAgent":"","strBirthLocation":"Curitiba, Brazil","strEthnicity":"Hispanic","strStatus":"Active","strDescriptionEN":"Marlon Adriano Prezotti (born 26 February 1990), simply known as Marlon, is a Brazilian professional footballer who plays as a midfielder for Juventude.\r\n\r\nBorn in Curitiba, Paraná, Marlon left his hometown at the age of 16 and subsequently joined Villa Nova's youth setup. In 2008, he moved to Cruzeiro, but returned to his former side Villa Nova on loan in the following year.\r\n\r\nMarlon made his professional debut on 2 March 2009, coming on as a second-half substitute for Wander Luiz in a 0–1 Campeonato Mineiro away loss against Uberaba. After featuring rarely, he subsequently served another loan stint at Formiga in 2011 before signing for Francana in 2012.\r\n\r\nIn June 2013, after representing Esportiva Guaxupé and Mamoré, Marlon moved to Sertãozinho. He then moved to Santa Rita for the 2014 Campeonato Alagoano before signing for ASA in May of that year.\r\n\r\nOn 13 January 2016, Marlon was presented at Caxias. He won the Campeonato Gaúcho Série A2 in that year with the club, and moved to Série C side Sampaio Corrêa in May 2017.\r\n\r\nOn 3 May 2018, Marlon agreed to a two-year deal with Fortaleza in the Série B, after the club paid his R$200,000 release clause. He quickly established as a regular starter for the side, helping in their promotion to the Série A and the subsequent two Campeonato Cearense titles, aside from the 2019 Copa do Nordeste winning campaign.\r\n\r\nOn 17 February 2021, free agent Marlon signed a two-year contract with Fortaleza's rivals Ceará.","strDescriptionDE":null,"strDescriptionFR":null,"strDescriptionCN":null,"strDescriptionIT":null,"strDescriptionJP":null,"strDescriptionRU":null,"strDescriptionES":null,"strDescriptionPT":null,"strDescriptionSE":null,"strDescriptionNL":null,"strDescriptionHU":null,"strDescriptionNO":null,"strDescriptionIL":null,"strDescriptionPL":null,"strGender":"Male","strSide":"","strPosition":"Central Midfield","strCollege":null,"strFacebook":"","strWebsite":"","strTwitter":"","strInstagram":"","strYoutube":"","strHeight":"175 cm","strWeight":"150 lbs","intLoved":"0","strThumb":null,"strPoster":null,"strCutout":null,"strCartoon":null,"strRender":null,"strBanner":null,"strFanart1":null,"strFanart2":null,"strFanart3":null,"strFanart4":null,"strCreativeCommons":"No","strLocked":"unlocked","strLastName":"Marlon"},{"idPlayer":"34197869","idTeam":"141182","idTeam2":null,"idTeamNational":null,"idAPIfootball":"9371","idPlayerManager":null,"idWikidata":"Q55760880","idTransferMkt":null,"idESPN":"273399","strNationality":"Brazil","strPlayer":"Nathan Fogaça","strPlayerAlternate":"","strTeam":"Novorizontino","strTeam2":"","strSport":"Soccer","intSoccerXMLTeamID":null,"dateBorn":"1999-06-09","dateDied":null,"strNumber":"99","dateSigned":null,"strSigning":"","strWage":"","strOutfitter":"","strKit":"","strAgent":"","strBirthLocation":"Palmeira, Brazil","strEthnicity":"Hispanic","strStatus":"Active","strDescriptionEN":"Nathan Uiliam Fogaça (born 9 June 1999), is a Brazilian professional footballer who plays as a forward for Novorizontino. \r\n\r\nCareer\r\nNathan came through the youth ranks at Coritiba and was called up to the senior side from the under-19s in May 2018. He made his professional debut a month later on 5 June 2018, coming on as a second-half substitute in the 1–0 2018 Campeonato Brasileiro Série B win against CRB. On 24 July 2018 he scored his first professional goal; the winner in the Série B match against Goiás. In April 2021, Fogaça joined American side San Antonio FC on loan for the 2021 season.\r\n\r\nIn April 2022, Fogaça was signed to a two-year contract by Portland Timbers 2.  A month later, he signed with the club's first team who compete in Major League Soccer.","strDescriptionDE":null,"strDescriptionFR":null,"strDescriptionCN":null,"strDescriptionIT":null,"strDescriptionJP":null,"strDescriptionRU":null,"strDescriptionES":null,"strDescriptionPT":null,"strDescriptionSE":null,"strDescriptionNL":null,"strDescriptionHU":null,"strDescriptionNO":null,"strDescriptionIL":null,"strDescriptionPL":null,"strGender":"Male","strSide":"","strPosition":"","strCollege":null,"strFacebook":"","strWebsite":"","strTwitter":"","strInstagram":"","strYoutube":"","strHeight":"178 cm (5 ft 10 in)","strWeight":"161 lbs","intLoved":"0","strThumb":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/thumb/kpwvuf1652781578.jpg","strPoster":null,"strCutout":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/cutout/8bv0s21719486680.png","strCartoon":null,"strRender":"https://r2.thesportsdb.com/images/media/player/render/z19om31652781720.png","strBanner":null,"strFanart1":null,"strFanart2":null,"strFanart3":null,"strFanart4":null,"strCreativeCommons":"No","strLocked":"unlocked","strLastName":"Fogaça"}]}